		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Since I am very busy to day I must<lb/> beg you to excuse me when I only acknowledge your<lb/> labour of last weeks&#44; and assure you that it grieves me<lb/> to think that you will probably retire from public<lb/> business&#59; every one laboring in the cause of Judaism may<lb/> say <add>Hebrew</add>.</p>
				<p>Good news in <placeName>Albany</placeName>.  My cause against <persName>Louis Spanier</persName><lb/> was decided on <add>Hebrew</add> before the Mayor&#39;s court<lb/> of this City.  I have fought the battle of all ministers in<lb/> this country and the victory <del>of th</del> is ours.</p>
				<list type="ordered">
				<head>The decisions of the Judge are</head>
				<item n="1">A minister elected by the majority of the Congregation<lb/> can be deposed only by a vote of said majority&#44; otherwise<lb/> none dare prevent him or interfere with him in the<lb/> discharge of his official duties.</item>
				<item n="2">All acts of a <add>Hebrew</add> <add>Parnass</add> without the consent of the majority<lb/> of trustees are illegal</item>
				<item n="3">The meeting of the Congregation Beth&#45;El on the <date>5. of<lb/> September</date> last is illegal and all resolutions passed<lb/> are null and void&#44; because 1. No notice was given&#44; that resolutions <del>shall</del> will be <del>passed</del> offered regarding the minster<lb/> of the Congregation<del>s</del>&#44; and still such resolutions were<lb/> passed at said meeting&#59; 2 motions were made and<lb/> seconded to adjourn the meeting&#44; which the chair<lb/> refused to put to the meeting&#59; in consequence of which the majority of the trustees after a delay of two hours<lb/> <sic>anounced</sic> the meeting adjourned&#44; to which the majority<lb/> of the congregation responded and left the meeting&#59;<lb/> only 43 out of the 132 members of the Congregation<lb/> remained and passed resolution concerning <persName role="author">Dr. Wise</persName>&#44;</item>
			<pb n="1V"/>
        <item n="4">The plaintiff <persName role="author">Isaac M. Wise</persName> DD. was bound in duty<lb/> to mount the pulpit on <date>Sabbath</date> next&#44; <date>September 7</date>&#44;<lb/> as he usually did&#44; and did so in a legal and orderly<lb/> manner.</item>
				<item n="5">The defendant<persName> Louis Spanier</persName> had no right to<lb/> interfere nor to stand at the pulpit.</item>
				<item n="6">The <del>plain f</del> defendant prevented <del>prevented</del> the<lb/> plaintiff from the discharge of his duty by inflicting<lb/> upon him blows and pushes.</item>
				<item n="7">The defendant is guilty of an <sic>insault</sic> &#38; battery<lb/> committed on a minister in the pulpit in the<lb/> presence of his congregation.</item>
				</list>
				<p>The jury then retired and brought in a verdict<lb/> of thousand dollars and costs.</p>
				<p>I wish you publish these 7 points as the court decided&#44;<lb/> that I be justified before the world&#59; let the world<lb/> know&#44; that not I but <persName>Louis Spanier</persName> created a riot<lb/> in a Synagogue on the first day of <add>Hebrew</add>&#59; let the<lb/> world also know&#44; that a <add>Hebrew</add> has no right to do<lb/> harm to a minister.  I have been defiled before<lb/> the world and I do ask of you to restore me by<lb/> publishing these facts&#44; as the court confirmed them.<lb/>  I am responsible as to the truth of these facts&#59; but<lb/> I do not wish to give my name as correspondent.</p>
				<p>My time forbids to write more.</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><sic>Truely</sic> yours</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Dr Wise</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Albany</placeName> <date>May 18. 1851</date></p>
			
